Scientists however face a number of challenges when working on CubeSats. Due to their size, CubeSats cannot power many of NASAâ€™s formidable scientific instruments, and there are limits to what can be miniaturized. The Hubble Space Telescope for example uses a mirror nearly eight feet wide to capture light and translate it into images that a smaller mirror could not produce.
